text:
570 Lexington Avenue, (General Electric Building) at the S.W. corner of E. 51st Street, (general view west).

Prominently shown are the No. 444 Madison Avenue, R.C.A. and International Buildings and St. Patricks Cathedral. In the foreground is an apartment house bearing No. 320-330 Park Avenue, and is on the west side of same, between E. 50th and 51st Streets.

1936

W. P. A.
Federal Writers Project
title: General view - [Manhattan - Lexington Avenue - 51st Street (East).]
